<br>
1.  Can't cast on pet if mag is levitated above water, and pet is fighting something underwater.    Spell casts as per normal, get no feedback (no fizz, no LoS message), but nothing happens.   Also, if I am above the water line, I can't nuke the mob under the water the pet is killing.<br>
<br>
(this has caused me no end of grief when trying to sneak up on raptor island).<br>
<br>
Basically, it looks like spells cant cross the water boundry, but that makes little sense.<br>
<br>
<br>
2.  %M doesn't work<br>
<br>
According to <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/manual/manual.jsp?id=46880">eqlive.station.sony.com/m...p?id=46880</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> %M returns the characters pet name.  Thus I figured this should work (for my cleric when duo with a mag)<br>
<br>
/target mag01<br>
/target %M<br>
/gs Healing a big blob of elemental material called %T<br>
/cast whatever<br>
<br>
Doesn't work, even wasted time putting in pauses.  try this:<br>
<br>
/target mag01<br>
/say pet name is %M<br>
<br>
seems pet name is always Pet.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/02 1:31:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7519.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mage Known Bug List?</span><hr size=1> Feninie,<br>
<br>
1) has been an issue for a long long time. they even claimed to have fixed it but the only thing they seem to have fixed is the &quot;you can't see your target from there&quot; message you used to get. Nobody is sure why you can't cast thru the water surface, however I suspect there must've been some pulling exploit issue from long long ago, during beta.<br>
<br>
2) the %M command returns the name of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>YOUR PET</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, not a pet you happen to have targeted. If you have no pet up it returns Pet. They don't always make that clear in their manuals and help screens. If the mage uses it, it works, but for the cleric it doesn't. The cleric needs to use the double F-key to target the pet and %T to get the pet name to show up in the healing macro. <p><br>
Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
